{"name": "evotree", "metadata": {"name": "evotree", "version": "0.0.0.1", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "http://github.com/heche-psb/evotree", "license": "GPL", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["biopython", "click", "pandas", "numpy", "rich", "matplotlib"], "summary": "Python package and CLI for processing phylogenetic tree", "upload_time": 1735476567}, "documentation": ["<div align=\"center\">\n\n# `evotree` : a python library of processing phylogenetic tree\n**Hengchi Chen**\n\n[**Installation**](#installation)\n</div>\n\n## Installation\nThe `fossiler` package can be readily installed via `PYPI`. An example command is given below.\n\n```\nvirtualenv -p=python3 ENV (or python3/python -m venv ENV)\nsource ENV/bin/activate\npip install evotree\n```\n\nNote that if users want to get the latest update, it's suggested to install from the source because the update on `PYPI` will be later than here of source. To install from source, the following command can be used.\n\n```\ngit clone https://github.com/heche-psb/evotree\ncd evotree\nvirtualenv -p=python3 ENV (or python3 -m venv ENV)\nsource ENV/bin/activate\npip install -r requirements.txt\npip install .\n```\n\nIf there is permission problem in the installation, please try the following command.\n\n```\npip install -e .\n```\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/python3.8", "contact: heche@psb.vib-ugent.be"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.long_description", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "command", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "command.cli", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "verbosity", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["evotree - Copyright (C) 2025-2026 Hengchi Chen\n\nContact: heche@psb.vib-ugent.be"]}, {"name": "command.initree", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tree", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "polar", "type": null, "default": nu